01:02:18,990 --> 01:02:24,950
"I know." That was all Eddie could say. He
was so tired. He rubbed his eyes.

830
01:02:24,950 --> 01:02:30,730
"So there's no position for you?" asked Clive,
but he could see the answer coming.

831
01:02:30,730 --> 01:02:32,800
"Right," said Eddie.

832
01:02:32,800 --> 01:02:35,780
"They're making you redundant, then?"

833
01:02:35,780 --> 01:02:36,780
"No."

834
01:02:36,780 --> 01:02:42,520
Clive was confused, and Eddie could not bring
himself to say any more. So Lynn continued

835
01:02:42,520 --> 01:02:45,970
for him. "They fired him," she said.

836
01:02:45,970 --> 01:02:48,190
There was a brief silence.

837
01:02:48,190 --> 01:02:50,030
"They what"

838
01:02:50,030 --> 01:02:54,600
"Can you believe it? It's disgusting," said
Lynn.

839
01:02:54,600 --> 01:02:58,470
Clive turned to Eddie. "I don't believe it,"
he said.

840
01:02:58,470 --> 01:03:02,260
"Neither do I," said Eddie, staring into space.

841
01:03:02,260 --> 01:03:04,420
"Fired for what?"

842
01:03:04,420 --> 01:03:10,330
"He's using the issue about the 25,000 pounds
in last year's budget, but he also said I

843
01:03:10,330 --> 01:03:14,170
was a negative influence on the project and
not hands-on enough'."

844
01:03:14,170 --> 01:03:21,660
"You have got to be joking!" Neither Eddie
nor Lynn said anything. It was no joke.

845
01:03:21,660 --> 01:03:27,610
"You're very hands-on. The other day he said
you were too hands-on, didn't he?"

846
01:03:27,610 --> 01:03:28,810
"Exactly," said Eddie.

847
01:03:28,810 --> 01:03:33,440
"And in what way are you negative? You are
more enthusiastic and positive than the two

848
01:03:33,440 --> 01:03:36,660
of them put together," said Clive.

849
01:03:36,660 --> 01:03:38,190
Eddie didn't say anything.

850
01:03:38,190 --> 01:03:44,860
"He just wants a yes-man," continued Clive.
"Neal is the true corporate yes-man. He plays

851
01:03:44,860 --> 01:03:50,030
the game and does what he's told. But he's
useless otherwise, and too frightened to say

852
01:03:50,030 --> 01:03:51,680
anything and rock the boat."

853
01:03:51,680 --> 01:03:53,660
"Who would want to be like that?"

854
01:03:53,660 --> 01:03:58,961
"These guys think they're above everyone else.
It's as simple as that. They have no idea

855
01:03:58,961 --> 01:04:04,150
what other people really think of them. They
either scare you so you won't tell them, or

856
01:04:04,150 --> 01:04:06,640
they just talk over you in case they look
weak."

857
01:04:06,640 --> 01:04:11,980
"Meanwhile, Neal gets a job and Eddie doesn't,"
said Lynn.

858
01:04:11,980 --> 01:04:18,330
"It's funny, but I really don't care anymore,"
said Eddie. "They deserve each other. I don't

859
01:04:18,330 --> 01:04:23,910
want to be a part of their grey world with
their grey suits and grey ideas. They have

860
01:04:23,910 --> 01:04:28,300
no imagination. Only a selfish need to justify
themselves."

861
01:04:28,300 --> 01:04:32,790
"They can't do this, surely?" Lynn asked Clive.

862
01:04:32,790 --> 01:04:34,860
"They can and they have."

863
01:04:34,860 --> 01:04:38,670
"But it's unfair dismissal. You can take them
to a tribunal."

864
01:04:38,670 --> 01:04:41,770
"I'm not sure I can cope with that," said
Eddie.

865
01:04:41,770 --> 01:04:45,630
"But you have to," said Lynn. "You've got
to fight it."

866
01:04:45,630 --> 01:04:51,310
"All I do with him is fight. Now he has Neal
to do his fighting. And he says he has the

867
01:04:51,310 --> 01:04:54,170
full support of Ann and Gary, so they're no
help."

868
01:04:54,170 --> 01:04:59,860
"You should have played more golf, Ed," said
Clive sarcastically.

869
01:04:59,860 --> 01:05:04,331
Eddie thought about that for a moment and
then said, "Now that I have no job, maybe

870
01:05:04,331 --> 01:05:07,000
I'll have the time."

871
01:05:07,000 --> 01:05:13,230
The next morning Eddie went into the office
early again to clear his desk. There were

872
01:05:13,230 --> 01:05:18,950
only a few people there. He saw Adam from
IT, who came over to him. He noticed Eddie

873
01:05:18,950 --> 01:05:22,480
was busy emptying drawers and throwing files
and old documents away.

874
01:05:22,480 --> 01:05:28,720
"Hi, Ed, how's it going? Doing a spring clean?
Good man. Long live the paperless office!"

875
01:05:28,720 --> 01:05:32,410
"Not exactly, Adam. I'm leaving, as a matter
of fact."

876
01:05:32,410 --> 01:05:36,040
"No way!" he said. "I had no idea."

877
01:05:36,040 --> 01:05:41,940
"Me neither," said Eddie, reaching for a folder
and glancing quickly at its contents. He got

878
01:05:41,940 --> 01:05:44,690
halfway through and then threw the folder
into the bin.

879
01:05:44,690 --> 01:05:46,440
"What's happened?"

880
01:05:46,440 --> 01:05:52,430
"I was fired yesterday," said Eddie. The words
sounded unreal when they came out.

881
01:05:52,430 --> 01:05:53,810
"What for?"

882
01:05:53,810 --> 01:05:55,200
"Oh, it doesn't matter."

883
01:05:55,200 --> 01:05:58,700
"You're one of the best people here, Ed. I
mean it."

884
01:05:58,700 --> 01:06:05,710
"Thanks, Adam, but they don't want the best
here. They just want..." Eddie stopped for

885
01:06:05,710 --> 01:06:12,070
a moment and looked across the office, deep
in thought. "You know what, Adam, I have absolutely

886
01:06:12,070 --> 01:06:17,550
no idea what they want." He turned and looked
at Adam. "And do you know what the worst thing

887
01:06:17,550 --> 01:06:18,550
is?"

888
01:06:18,550 --> 01:06:19,550
"What?"

889
01:06:19,550 --> 01:06:24,820
"They don't know either. My guess is they
just want to be in charge. Nothing else matters.

890
01:06:24,820 --> 01:06:30,140
They just want to move people around and feel
important," said Eddie, slamming a cupboard

891
01:06:30,140 --> 01:06:35,040
door shut and pushing his chair away from
the desk. "They don't think about the people,

892
01:06:35,040 --> 01:06:40,310
their work, their customers. They don't care
about loyalty. They don't care about building

893
01:06:40,310 --> 01:06:46,170
a business. They talk, have meetings and play
golf, but they don't know the business and

894
01:06:46,170 --> 01:06:49,030
they know they need us to make it work."

895
01:06:49,030 --> 01:06:55,290
"You know your problem," came a voice from
behind them. "You were never a corporate man,

896
01:06:55,290 --> 01:06:56,290
Eddie."

897
01:06:56,290 --> 01:07:01,720
It was Neal. Eddie was completely taken by
surprise. He was both embarrassed and furious

898
01:07:01,720 --> 01:07:03,540
to see him standing there.

899
01:07:03,540 --> 01:07:08,770
Adam started walking away. "Look, Ed, I'll
catch you later," he said. "Let's have a drink

900
01:07:08,770 --> 01:07:10,740
before you go, OK?"

901
01:07:10,740 --> 01:07:15,840
"Sure," said Eddie, who decided to ignore
Neal and finish clearing his desk.

902
01:07:15,840 --> 01:07:21,260
"You need the skin of a crocodile in this
business, I'm telling you." Eddie tried to

903
01:07:21,260 --> 01:07:27,650
ignore him and carried on throwing away files,
paper, software manuals. Everything.

904
01:07:27,650 --> 01:07:34,650
"Besides," continued Neal, "Dominic needs
someone like me. Someone more... academic.

905
01:07:34,650 --> 01:07:40,840
He needs someone who can talk to him." Eddie
stopped and looked at him. Was there no end

906
01:07:40,840 --> 01:07:43,480
to Neal's patronizing arrogance?

907
01:07:43,480 --> 01:07:48,870
"Neal, you're deceiving yourself. Dominic
wants a yes-man. Pure and simple. Now he's

908
01:07:48,870 --> 01:07:50,830
got one. Congratulations."

909
01:07:50,830 --> 01:07:52,620
"You're upset."

910
01:07:52,620 --> 01:07:56,510
"No, really? Amazing. How did you guess?"

911
01:07:56,510 --> 01:08:01,120
"Look, I don't have a problem with you. It's
nothing personal."

912
01:08:01,120 --> 01:08:06,490
"That's so generous of you, Neal. I feel so
much better," said Eddie, moving up close

913
01:08:06,490 --> 01:08:13,050
to him. He could smell Neal's stale cigarette
breath. "Well, I have a big problem with you,

914
01:08:13,050 --> 01:08:20,239
and, believe it or not, I am taking this very
personally. I guess I'm human, not a crocodile.

915
01:08:20,239 --> 01:08:21,670
What would you rather be?"

916
01:08:21,670 --> 01:08:24,569
"I know how you feel," said Neal.

917
01:08:24,569 --> 01:08:30,699
"You have no idea how I feel, and don't talk
to me about how to talk to people like Dominic.

918
01:08:30,699 --> 01:08:37,049
He needs someone more academic, indeed. What
does that mean? And corporate. What is corporate?"

919
01:08:37,049 --> 01:08:39,650
"You have to play the game, Eddie."

920
01:08:39,650 --> 01:08:44,309
"Maybe. But I'm not interested if the end
result is turning into a grey yes-man like

921
01:08:44,309 --> 01:08:50,409
you. Ask yourself the question: are you true
to yourself? I wonder."

922
01:08:50,409 --> 01:08:57,119
"Nice, Eddie. Very professional," said Neal,
finally showing his irritation.

923
01:08:57,119 --> 01:09:03,180
"And you know all about professional, do you?
Open your eyes. Really open your eyes. Listen

924
01:09:03,180 --> 01:09:08,409
to what people say about you. You're deceiving
yourself and I actually feel sorry for you.

925
01:09:08,409 --> 01:09:15,230
And if you want a second opinion, go and ask
people here or your old friends at Gallagher's."

926
01:09:15,230 --> 01:09:20,559
Neal was walking away now, so Eddie shouted
after him: "Did they give you a good reference,

927
01:09:20,559 --> 01:09:27,549
by the way? It wasn't redundancy, was it?"
Eddie carried on putting things in his bag

928
01:09:27,549 --> 01:09:32,210
before sitting down to write an email to all
his customers and colleagues to inform them

929
01:09:32,210 --> 01:09:34,869
of his departure.

930
01:09:34,869 --> 01:09:36,440
CHAPTER NINE
The fight

931
01:09:36,440 --> 01:09:44,369
As Dominic Stephens came out of the hotel
towards them, Eddie froze. He looked at Lynn

932
01:09:44,369 --> 01:09:49,859
and her face said the same. Before they could
make an excuse to leave, Dominic was already

933
01:09:49,859 --> 01:09:56,050
on the cafe terrace. His hair was grey and
combed back, and he was wearing white trousers,

934
01:09:56,050 --> 01:10:02,199
grey golf shoes and a green polo shirt which
was too tight for his large stomach.

935
01:10:02,199 --> 01:10:08,059
It was definitely Dominic. The same hard face
but now with a dark tan, though his chin and

936
01:10:08,059 --> 01:10:13,640
cheeks were fuller than the last time Eddie
had seen him. He looked older and different.

937
01:10:13,640 --> 01:10:21,860
"Hello, everyone. New friends, I see," he
said, putting out his hand. In a reflex action,

938
01:10:21,860 --> 01:10:27,559
Eddie noticed his hand go out to shake Dominic's.
He instantly felt he had betrayed himself.

939
01:10:27,559 --> 01:10:33,389
Dominic's handshake had not changed: his palm
at an angle, the fingers locked tight, difficult

940
01:10:33,389 --> 01:10:36,849
to grip. Do Not Enter, it said.

941
01:10:36,849 --> 01:10:43,510
Again, automatically, Eddie lifted his sunglasses
to be polite, but Dominic kept his on. Eddie

942
01:10:43,510 --> 01:10:49,090
waited for the moment when Dominic would recognise
him. But he did not. This cannot be true,

943
01:10:49,090 --> 01:10:54,480
he thought. Is this really Dominic? After
all this time, am I shaking hands with him

944
01:10:54,480 --> 01:11:00,579
and he does not know me? He looked at Lynn,
who was shaking his hand, too. Eddie could

945
01:11:00,579 --> 01:11:02,999
see that she was not comfortable either.

946
01:11:02,999 --> 01:11:07,650
"Nice to meet you," she said, putting on her
best smile.

947
01:11:07,650 --> 01:11:13,000
"How was the tennis?" Dominic asked, leaning
on the back of Jen's chair.

948
01:11:13,000 --> 01:11:17,590
"Cancelled," she said. "Then I met Lynn and
we've been working hard on cocktails since

949
01:11:17,590 --> 01:11:18,999
we got here."

950
01:11:18,999 --> 01:11:22,499
"Ah, it's a hard life," he said.

951
01:11:22,499 --> 01:11:28,760
Yes, thought Eddie. It can be very hard. And
some people make it harder. His head was quickly

952
01:11:28,760 --> 01:11:33,320
filling up with flashes of memory. Angry words
and images.

953
01:11:33,320 --> 01:11:38,019
"So, what are you guys going to do?" asked
Dominic.

954
01:11:38,019 --> 01:11:41,090
"Er, we've got to get back to the ship," said
Eddie.

955
01:11:41,090 --> 01:11:44,050
"I thought you were staying for the free lunch,"
said Jen.

956
01:11:44,050 --> 01:11:48,800
"Ah, there's no such thing as a free lunch,
eh, Eddie?"

957
01:11:48,800 --> 01:11:54,199
Eddie wasn't sure if Dominic had recognised
him. Maybe. Maybe not. Or maybe he was unsure

958
01:11:54,199 --> 01:11:58,820
and was playing for time? He never showed
much emotion, and behind the dark glasses

959
01:11:58,820 --> 01:12:00,789
he looked almost robotic.

960
01:12:00,789 --> 01:12:06,860
"I don't really know," said Eddie. He was
still trying to recover from the shock of

961
01:12:06,860 --> 01:12:10,429
Dominic standing there in front of him after
so long.

962
01:12:10,429 --> 01:12:16,869
"Sure. I've been in business twenty-five years
and I can tell you no lunch is free."

963
01:12:16,869 --> 01:12:21,020
"Right," said Eddie. "Right, well, nice to
meet you both."

964
01:12:21,020 --> 01:12:24,040
"Come on," said Jen, "stay for lunch."

965
01:12:24,040 --> 01:12:27,999
"No, really, I've had too much sun, I think,"
said Eddie.

966
01:12:27,999 --> 01:12:31,179
"Well, we can sit in the shade," said Jen.

967
01:12:31,179 --> 01:12:35,510
"No, I mean I don't feel too well," Eddie
said.

968
01:12:35,510 --> 01:12:40,530
"Hmm..." said Dominic, finally lifting up
his glasses and having a good look at Eddie's

969
01:12:40,530 --> 01:12:47,280
face, "... your nose is burnt, but you do
look quite pale otherwise. You look like you've

970
01:12:47,280 --> 01:12:49,789
seen a ghost."

971
01:12:49,789 --> 01:12:56,239
Eddie looked into Dominic's eyes. He did not
see any signs of recognition. He looked away.

972
01:12:56,239 --> 01:13:00,270
"Right. Yes. Anyway. Lynn?" he said.

973
01:13:00,270 --> 01:13:03,699
"Yes," she said, standing up. "I'm coming."

974
01:13:03,699 --> 01:13:07,929
"Well, maybe we could meet for a drink after
I finish tonight?" asked Jen.

975
01:13:07,929 --> 01:13:11,409
"She's a great singer, isn't she?" said Dominic.

976
01:13:11,409 --> 01:13:13,409
"Yes," said Eddie.

977
01:13:13,409 --> 01:13:14,780
"Wonderful," said Lynn.

978
01:13:14,780 --> 01:13:20,170
'I'm off at about eleven, so I'll come over
to the bar and we can meet you both then."

979
01:13:20,170 --> 01:13:23,619
"We'll see how Ed feels," said Lynn.

980
01:13:23,619 --> 01:13:30,760
Sure. Well, tomorrow then? Or breakfast?"
Dominic was laughing. "We're stuck together

981
01:13:30,760 --> 01:13:36,449
on the ship for the next two weeks, so there's
no getting away, is there?"

982
01:13:36,449 --> 01:13:41,280
Eddie had never imagined Dominic on holiday.
He only remembered that Dominic always came

983
01:13:41,280 --> 01:13:46,800
back from holidays complaining about the children.
"Ah, it's good to be back in the office,"

984
01:13:46,800 --> 01:13:52,630
he used to say, "away, from the kids." Eddie
felt sorry for Dominic's family whenever he

985
01:13:52,630 --> 01:13:54,300
heard him say that.

986
01:13:54,300 --> 01:13:59,869
"What would his kids say if they heard him
say that?" Eddie had once asked Clive. "Why

987
01:13:59,869 --> 01:14:04,400
did he have kids or a family at all if he
preferred to be in an office?"

988
01:14:04,400 --> 01:14:09,050
"Because these guys like to be the center
of the universe, and kids and partners take

989
01:14:09,050 --> 01:14:14,619
that away from them. Besides, family life
and kids are all about showing emotion, and

990
01:14:14,619 --> 01:14:20,679
they find it too scary. That's why they hide
behind desks and power. Can you imagine Dominic

991
01:14:20,679 --> 01:14:25,239
or Neal trying to be with their kids? They
don't know how. They probably didn't know

992
01:14:25,239 --> 01:14:28,000
how to be with kids when they were kids."

993
01:14:28,000 --> 01:14:30,920
"That's so sad," Eddie had said.

994
01:14:30,920 --> 01:14:36,579
"They are sad. They've missed the best things
in life and think money and status are enough.

995
01:14:36,579 --> 01:14:41,349
But they are so superior in their own minds
that they don't know it."

996
01:14:41,349 --> 01:14:44,329
"So they're actually happy? Ignorance is happiness?"

997
01:14:44,329 --> 01:14:51,560
"Maybe. I'm not so sure. How often do you
see these guys relax, laugh or even smile?"

998
01:14:51,560 --> 01:14:52,560
"True."

999
01:14:52,560 --> 01:14:54,110
"Well, there's your answer."

1000
01:14:54,110 --> 01:15:03,749
"Eddie?" Lynn's voice suddenly brought Eddie
back to reality. "Eddie? Are you coming?"

1001
01:15:03,749 --> 01:15:08,020
"Yeah. Sorry," he said. "See you guys later."

1002
01:15:08,020 --> 01:15:12,350
"Bye," said Jen and Dominic together.

1003
01:15:12,350 --> 01:15:17,010
Eddie and Lynn walked back through the hotel
to the taxis. As they went back to the port

1004
01:15:17,010 --> 01:15:19,600
and the ship, Lynn spoke first.

1005
01:15:19,600 --> 01:15:20,600
"Well?"

1006
01:15:20,600 --> 01:15:26,660
"He looks older. He's still got that arrogant
look. And he's put on a lot of weight." Eddie

1007
01:15:26,660 --> 01:15:28,099
glanced out of the window.

1008
01:15:28,099 --> 01:15:31,599
"Are they married, do you think? What happened
to his wife?"

1009
01:15:31,599 --> 01:15:36,499
"Don't know," said Eddie. "I hope she left
him. For her sake."

1010
01:15:36,499 --> 01:15:39,920
"I wonder what Jen is doing with a man like
him, then?"

1011
01:15:39,920 --> 01:15:42,809
"Goodness knows. He's old enough to be her
father."

1012
01:15:42,809 --> 01:15:48,920
The taxi moved along the harbour and passed
the yachts in the marina. Eddie was shaking

1013
01:15:48,920 --> 01:15:49,980
his head in disbelief.

1014
01:15:49,980 --> 01:15:54,030
"I don't believe it, Lynn," he said. "Can
you believe it?"

1015
01:15:54,030 --> 01:15:59,800
"No. But at least he doesn't remember you,"
she said, looking at him. Eddie kept staring

1016
01:15:59,800 --> 01:16:05,469
out of the window. "Do you think not?" he
said. "Oh, come on. It's over sixteen years,

1017
01:16:05,469 --> 01:16:09,420
Ed. If he had remembered you, he would have
said something - don't you think?"

1018
01:16:09,420 --> 01:16:16,260
"Not necessarily. You never know with him.
I never knew with him. He's a snake. A fat

1019
01:16:16,260 --> 01:16:18,019
snake now, of course. But still a snake."

1020
01:16:18,019 --> 01:16:21,429
"Maybe he's changed," said Lynn hopefully.

1021
01:16:21,429 --> 01:16:23,559
"I doubt it."

1022
01:16:23,559 --> 01:16:29,010
The taxi slowed down and stopped near the
gangway for the Parvina. They paid the driver

1023
01:16:29,010 --> 01:16:30,570
and got out.

1024
01:16:30,570 --> 01:16:36,690
"It doesn't matter if he's an angel now. I'll
never forgive him. The three things I hate

1025
01:16:36,690 --> 01:16:41,730
most in the world are arrogance, bullying
and betrayal. He's guilty of all three."

1026
01:16:41,730 --> 01:16:47,130
"Well, let's hope he doesn't remember you.
We don't have to see them anyway."

1027
01:16:47,130 --> 01:16:53,410
"He's with the singer of the ship's band,
Lynn - we'll see him every night!" Lynn walked

1028
01:16:53,410 --> 01:16:59,440
in silence on to the ship and into the reception
deck. What could she say?

1029
01:16:59,440 --> 01:17:03,449
That night Eddie and Lynn had dinner in the
main dining room, which was full, as it was

1030
01:17:03,449 --> 01:17:08,679
every night. As the sun went down and the
room got darker, Eddie found it harder to

1031
01:17:08,679 --> 01:17:14,409
see if Dominic was in the room or not. Throughout
dinner he had expected him to turn up, but

1032
01:17:14,409 --> 01:17:15,480
he was not there.

1033
01:17:15,480 --> 01:17:20,570
As they finished dessert and drank their coffee,
however, Dominic appeared and took a seat

1034
01:17:20,570 --> 01:17:22,289
at the bar to watch Jen.

1035
01:17:22,289 --> 01:17:24,829
"There he is," said Eddie.

1036
01:17:24,829 --> 01:17:29,280
"Oh yes. Well, maybe we could go back to the
cabin, or the casino."

1037
01:17:29,280 --> 01:17:33,639
"No, Lynn. We're not letting him push us around
again."

1038
01:17:33,639 --> 01:17:36,150
"But he'll soon see us and come over."

1039
01:17:36,150 --> 01:17:38,949
"I doubt it. He was always antisocial."

1040
01:17:38,949 --> 01:17:41,150
"Maybe he's changed."

1041
01:17:41,150 --> 01:17:46,039
"You keep saying that. People like him never
change."

1042
01:17:46,039 --> 01:17:51,010
Eddie sipped his coffee and said, "I think
I need to know for sure if he remembers me.

1043
01:17:51,010 --> 01:17:52,039
I'd feel a lot happier."

1044
01:17:52,039 --> 01:17:56,499
"But why, Ed? What good will that do?" she
asked.

1045
01:17:56,499 --> 01:17:58,300
"I can't explain."

1046
01:17:58,300 --> 01:18:03,830
"Eddie, please... Look, he's leaving anyway.
He's not going to bother us."

1047
01:18:03,830 --> 01:18:08,400
But Eddie had already got up from the table
and was walking over to the bar and the exit

1048
01:18:08,400 --> 01:18:09,739
to follow him.

1049
01:18:09,739 --> 01:18:14,369
He followed Dominic down the corridor and
past the Starlight Lounge, where people were

1050
01:18:14,369 --> 01:18:19,880
playing cards and reading. He followed him
through the door, out on to the side deck

1051
01:18:19,880 --> 01:18:25,210
and to the stern of the ship. It was dark,
and Eddie thought he had lost him. But then

1052
01:18:25,210 --> 01:18:31,400
he swelled the unmistakable cigar smoke and
he saw him. The earlier breeze had been replaced

1053
01:18:31,400 --> 01:18:38,389
by a strong wind and the sea was quite rough.
He noticed Dominic in a small area, alone,

1054
01:18:38,389 --> 01:18:42,929
sheltered from the wind, leaning on to the
rail and looking out to sea.

1055
01:18:42,929 --> 01:18:46,070
"Hello," said Eddie, walking up to him.

1056
01:18:46,070 --> 01:18:49,630
"Oh, hello there. Getting some fresh air?"

1057
01:18:49,630 --> 01:18:50,809
"I suppose so."

1058
01:18:50,809 --> 01:18:56,929
"Me too," said Dominic. "Feeling better?"
he asked.

1059
01:18:56,929 --> 01:18:58,510
"Yes, thanks."

1060
01:18:58,510 --> 01:19:03,369
They both looked out to sea together for a
long minute. Eddie broke the silence.

1061
01:19:03,369 --> 01:19:08,010
"You don't remember me, do you?" he asked,
looking at Dominic.

1062
01:19:08,010 --> 01:19:14,199
"Yes, I just asked if you were feeling better.
We met at the hotel today. Your wife's tennis

1063
01:19:14,199 --> 01:19:15,199
was cancelled."

1064
01:19:15,199 --> 01:19:19,159
"No, not here. Back home. At work."

1065
01:19:19,159 --> 01:19:25,460
"What do you mean?" asked Dominic, looking
at Eddie. "Where?"

1066
01:19:25,460 --> 01:19:31,140
Eddie knew Dominic had been in many companies.
Creeping his way in, then getting thrown out.

1067
01:19:31,140 --> 01:19:35,710
Dominic called them redundancies. Others knew
better.

1068
01:19:35,710 --> 01:19:37,660
"Fenton's."

1069
01:19:37,660 --> 01:19:41,429
Dominic looked at him and then looked harder,
using the light coming from the spotlight

1070
01:19:41,429 --> 01:19:46,150
on the wall. "What's your surname?" he asked.

1071
01:19:46,150 --> 01:19:47,880
"Munro."

1072
01:19:47,880 --> 01:19:49,780
Dominic appeared to be trying to remember.

1073
01:19:49,780 --> 01:19:54,460
"I was in sales. There was the big project
at Zariya in Moscow."

1074
01:19:54,460 --> 01:20:05,139
"Ah," said Dominic. "Eddie Munro. Yes." He
smoked his cigar some more, buying time. "When

1075
01:20:05,139 --> 01:20:07,510
was that?" he asked finally.

1076
01:20:07,510 --> 01:20:10,099
"Sixteen years ago."

1077
01:20:10,099 --> 01:20:13,159
"Wow, good memory," said Dominic.

1078
01:20:13,159 --> 01:20:19,119
"Not really..." said Eddie, "... you fired
me and it's not something one forgets."

1079
01:20:19,119 --> 01:20:25,849
"Did I?" and Dominic actually laughed. Over
the years Eddie had imagined meeting him again

1080
01:20:25,849 --> 01:20:29,579
and confronting him. He had never imagined
the man laughing.

1081
01:20:29,579 --> 01:20:35,860
"You did, yes. You found a way to blame me
for a budget loss of 25,000 pounds."

1082
01:20:35,860 --> 01:20:41,820
"It's a long time ago. I honestly can't remember,"
said Dominic, still smoking, looking back

1083
01:20:41,820 --> 01:20:47,670
at the sea. Eddie was staring at him. His
mouth was dry. He was trembling.

1084
01:20:47,670 --> 01:20:49,659
"Well, I remember."

1085
01:20:49,659 --> 01:20:54,949
"Good for you," said Dominic, and now his
tone was changing.

1086
01:20:54,949 --> 01:20:57,480
Less interested. Colder.

1087
01:20:57,480 --> 01:21:04,110
"Actually, I remember you were an incompetent
bully. You made my life miserable."

1088
01:21:04,110 --> 01:21:09,900
Dominic turned around and looked at Eddie.
"Is that so?" It was too dark to see if he

1089
01:21:09,900 --> 01:21:14,530
was angry or not. Eddie felt that the situation
was getting out of control, but there was

1090
01:21:14,530 --> 01:21:17,820
no turning back. The words were coming out
on their own.

1091
01:21:17,820 --> 01:21:24,530
"I was very successful at Fenton's," said
Dominic firmly, "and one reason was probably

1092
01:21:24,530 --> 01:21:28,550
because I was able to get rid of useless rubbish
like you."

1093
01:21:28,550 --> 01:21:33,690
"They fired you from there eventually, I heard.
Why was that?"

1094
01:21:33,690 --> 01:21:39,710
Dominic started walking away. "An interesting
reunion, my friend, but it's late and I'm

1095
01:21:39,710 --> 01:21:45,619
bored with this conversation. I suggest you
leave the past in the past and move on."

1096
01:21:45,619 --> 01:21:49,130
Eddie grabbed his arm. He felt Dominic's body
stiffen.

1097
01:21:49,130 --> 01:21:54,550
"Get your hands off me," Dominic said, putting
his cigar in his mouth to free his hand.

1098
01:21:54,550 --> 01:22:01,710
"I moved on, Dominic. I moved on after you
took away my job, my money, my peace of mind

1099
01:22:01,710 --> 01:22:04,300
and almost my wife."

1100
01:22:04,300 --> 01:22:08,159
Eddie was angry now. The words were not coming
out right any more.

1101
01:22:08,159 --> 01:22:15,039
"I've seen your wife, Eddie," Dominic said,
laughing. "I can tell you that you still need

1102
01:22:15,039 --> 01:22:16,639
to move on."

1103
01:22:16,639 --> 01:22:22,369
"What does that mean?" This time Eddie pushed
him against the rail of the ship and hit the

1104
01:22:22,369 --> 01:22:28,429
cigar out of Dominic's mouth. The light was
shining on Dominic's face, and Eddie saw a

1105
01:22:28,429 --> 01:22:30,420
mixture of surprise and anger.

1106
01:22:30,420 --> 01:22:36,079
"Hey! What is your problem?!" he shouted,
but they were out on deck in the wind and

1107
01:22:36,079 --> 01:22:41,050
darkness and it was like a whisper. Dominic
pushed back against the rail, but Eddie would

1108
01:22:41,050 --> 01:22:42,810
not let him move.

1109
01:22:42,810 --> 01:22:48,900
"You! You are my problem!" Eddie shouted.
He had no idea what he was doing any more.

1110
01:22:48,900 --> 01:22:52,510
He was scared, and angrier than he had been
for a long time.

1111
01:22:52,510 --> 01:22:55,550
"Move away, Eddie. This is unacceptable."

1112
01:22:55,550 --> 01:23:03,619
"Unacceptable? Unacceptable? Oh, really? So,
after all these years you know what is acceptable

1113
01:23:03,619 --> 01:23:10,469
and unacceptable. What you and Neal Skinner
did to me was unacceptable. The way you patronized

1114
01:23:10,469 --> 01:23:18,320
and intimidated me was unacceptable. You cheated
and lied. You were so smug, so superior."

1115
01:23:18,320 --> 01:23:24,309
"I was the boss. I made tough decisions. You
were a casualty. It happens in business. Sink

1116
01:23:24,309 --> 01:23:27,650
or swim, my friend. Get over it."

1117
01:23:27,650 --> 01:23:33,420
Without thinking, Eddie brought his knee hard
and fast up into Dominic's groin. Dominic

1118
01:23:33,420 --> 01:23:38,039
shouted out in shock and blinding pain, but
was able to push his hand hard into Eddie's

1119
01:23:38,039 --> 01:23:43,679
face. Eddie lost his balance for a moment,
giving Dominic time to stand up straight.

1120
01:23:43,679 --> 01:23:48,880
Dominic pushed Eddie in the chest, but Eddie
did not feel it. He was too busy getting his

1121
01:23:48,880 --> 01:23:54,769
hands around Dominic's neck. He squeezed and
squeezed, and Dominic tried to get himself

1122
01:23:54,769 --> 01:24:00,320
free. But he could not. Eddie's hands were
locked around Dominic's throat. He dug in

1123
01:24:00,320 --> 01:24:05,679
his nails to be sure. He pressed his thumbs.
Dominic was trying to speak, but he couldn't.

1124
01:24:05,679 --> 01:24:09,789
He choked out some words but Eddie could make
no sense of them.

1125
01:24:09,789 --> 01:24:18,730
"Just shut up! Shut up! You stupid... arrogant
man!" Eddie growled at him.

1126
01:24:18,730 --> 01:24:23,630
Eddie could finally see fear in Dominic's
face, which had gone pale, and his eyes stared

1127
01:24:23,630 --> 01:24:28,560
back at him. Eddie could see he was going
to pass out, so he loosened his grip. What

1128
01:24:28,560 --> 01:24:31,940
am I doing? he thought. This is madness.

1129
01:24:31,940 --> 01:24:38,010
But the moment he let go, pain suddenly shot
into Eddie's ear as Dominic threw a punch

1130
01:24:38,010 --> 01:24:43,551
to the right side of Eddie's head, and then
to his right side into his ribs. Eddie was

1131
01:24:43,551 --> 01:24:49,440
wild and angry once more, this time pushing
Dominic back on to the ship's rail. Hard against

1132
01:24:49,440 --> 01:24:56,789
the rail. Fast against the rail. Dominic shouting
in pain once more. Eddie punching and punching.

1133
01:24:56,789 --> 01:25:07,079
"OK, OK, enough, enough. Stop," pleaded Dominic,
his arms up in defense.

1134
01:25:07,079 --> 01:25:12,260
Eddie stopped. He loosened his grip again
and waited for a reaction from Dominic, but

1135
01:25:12,260 --> 01:25:19,300
none came. Eddie stood back and watched Dominic
try to stand up against the rail. Dominic

1136
01:25:19,300 --> 01:25:24,739
was holding his stomach and breathing heavily.
He coughed a couple of times. His head was

1137
01:25:24,739 --> 01:25:26,699
down.

1138
01:25:26,699 --> 01:25:32,239
Eddie was out of breath himself. He hadn't
been in a fight since he was fifteen. It felt

1139
01:25:32,239 --> 01:25:39,360
just the same even as an adult - tiring, frightening
and sore. That time there was a crowd watching.

1140
01:25:39,360 --> 01:25:41,840
This time there was no one.

1141
01:25:41,840 --> 01:25:50,880
"Don't come near me or speak to me again...
ever. Do you hear me?"

1142
01:25:50,880 --> 01:25:55,539
Dominic was still trying to get his breath.
Either he could not speak or he did not want

1143
01:25:55,539 --> 01:26:01,511
to. But he said nothing. Eddie took one last
look at him and backed away until he was at

1144
01:26:01,511 --> 01:26:06,429
a safe distance. Then he left the deck and
went back inside.

1145
01:26:06,429 --> 01:26:12,659
That was the last time anyone ever saw Dominic
Stephens.

1146
01:26:12,659 --> 01:26:17,449
CHAPTER TEN
Sinking not swimming

1147
01:26:17,449 --> 01:26:22,909
For a few days after his dismissal from Fenton's,
Eddie actually felt quite excited. He was

1148
01:26:22,909 --> 01:26:28,510
relieved. A great weight had been lifted from
his shoulders. But this feeling did not last

1149
01:26:28,510 --> 01:26:34,340
long, and he soon started to feel irritable
and, later on, angry.

1150
01:26:34,340 --> 01:26:39,800
For weeks he couldn't get Fenton's and Neal
and Dominic out of his mind. He thought over

1151
01:26:39,800 --> 01:26:46,070
and over again about the injustice of it all.
He thought about all the arguments and frustrations.

1152
01:26:46,070 --> 01:26:51,679
All the work he had done. All the work he
could have done. Wasted. He missed his colleagues

1153
01:26:51,679 --> 01:26:56,739
and a sense of belonging, and he missed going
to Russia and working with Dima and the team.

1154
01:26:56,739 --> 01:27:02,760
To cheer himself up, he tried to remind himself
that, apart from people like Dominic, there

1155
01:27:02,760 --> 01:27:08,519
were things he would not miss, like emails.
On the day Eddie left Fenton's for the last

1156
01:27:08,519 --> 01:27:14,820
time, there were over four hundred unanswered
emails in his inbox. Eddie always tried to

1157
01:27:14,820 --> 01:27:20,920
get back to people, but it had become impossible.
Every time he got rid of one email, a dozen

1158
01:27:20,920 --> 01:27:26,469
more would appear within half an hour. The
world had gone mad, he thought. At first,

1159
01:27:26,469 --> 01:27:31,840
like everyone else, Eddie had welcomed the
new form of communication. It was neat, cheap,

1160
01:27:31,840 --> 01:27:37,960
fast and flexible. But soon it dragged him
down. He didn't like to admit it, but Dominic

1161
01:27:37,960 --> 01:27:40,999
was right about not reading emails. They were
never-ending.

1162
01:27:40,999 --> 01:27:42,400
Dominic.

1163
01:27:42,400 --> 01:27:46,670
Back in his mind again.

1164
01:27:46,670 --> 01:27:50,600
Many times he had terrible thoughts about
what he would like to do to Dominic, and to

1165
01:27:50,600 --> 01:27:55,610
Neal for that matter. He thought of storming
into the office and using Dominic's own golf

1166
01:27:55,610 --> 01:28:01,010
clubs to smash up computers and break windows,
and then going into the car park and doing

1167
01:28:01,010 --> 01:28:07,369
his worst on Dominic's Mercedes. The shiny
paintwork, the windows - all slashed, scratched

1168
01:28:07,369 --> 01:28:13,519
and broken. It felt good but his conscience
would not let him.

1169
01:28:13,519 --> 01:28:17,780
In the end, he followed Lynn's advice, which
was to get out of the house more and go for

1170
01:28:17,780 --> 01:28:23,389
walks, or go swimming. Keep busy. Get some
exercise. They lived two miles from their

1171
01:28:23,389 --> 01:28:27,949
local sports center, so every morning Eddie
got up with Lynn and then walked through the

1172
01:28:27,949 --> 01:28:32,940
park to the pool at the sports center. He
made this his morning routine, but he couldn't

1173
01:28:32,940 --> 01:28:38,130
get used to being in a swimming pool on a
weekday morning at 10 a.m. He normally swam

1174
01:28:38,130 --> 01:28:43,420
after work, so it was strange for him to find
the pool almost empty, except for some elderly

1175
01:28:43,420 --> 01:28:49,349
swimmers and sometimes small school groups.
As he sat in the cafe afterwards, drinking

1176
01:28:49,349 --> 01:28:55,469
a coffee or two, he always felt better. He
wanted to stay there all day and hide. Then

1177
01:28:55,469 --> 01:28:59,250
his heart would sink at the thought of heading
home to nothing.

1178
01:28:59,250 --> 01:29:04,820
In fairness, Eddie had started looking for
jobs in the same week that he was fired. But

1179
01:29:04,820 --> 01:29:13,079
as depression set in, he lost interest and
motivation. Then, to his alarm, he lost confidence.

1180
01:29:13,079 --> 01:29:18,050
In a way, this was worse than the depression,
but these were all new feelings and he was

1181
01:29:18,050 --> 01:29:22,929
overwhelmed. Everything he had done seemed
meaningless, and he wondered how he would

1182
01:29:22,929 --> 01:29:25,760
ever do a serious job again.

1183
01:29:25,760 --> 01:29:31,380
He and Lynn had enough money saved to last
for about four months, but the time soon passed

1184
01:29:31,380 --> 01:29:36,249
and there were no vacancies. His chances with
the best companies in his sector were also

1185
01:29:36,249 --> 01:29:40,690
harmed by the news of his dismissal over the
budget fiasco.

1186
01:29:40,690 --> 01:29:47,599
By the time there were a couple of opportunities,
Eddie was physically unwell and his doctor

1187
01:29:47,599 --> 01:29:53,599
had agreed he was not fit for work. It took
time for sickness benefits to be paid, and

1188
01:29:53,599 --> 01:29:58,789
with the two of them living on Lynn's small
teaching salary the financial pressures grew.

1189
01:29:58,789 --> 01:30:04,650
Bills turned into reminders. Reminders turned
into final reminders. And final reminders

1190
01:30:04,650 --> 01:30:11,659
became phone calls from angry gas and electricity
companies, TV companies and insurance companies.

1191
01:30:11,659 --> 01:30:17,630
Then finally the bank called. Eddie was having
a bad day anyway. This was the last thing

1192
01:30:17,630 --> 01:30:18,780
he needed.

1193
01:30:18,780 --> 01:30:26,249
"Hello, Mr Munro, this is CNTS bank. May I
ask you some security questions?" said a young

1194
01:30:26,249 --> 01:30:27,249
male voice.

1195
01:30:27,249 --> 01:30:31,619
"Not really," said Eddie. He almost hung up
straight away.

1196
01:30:31,619 --> 01:30:36,900
"I just want to ask you some security questions
and then talk to you about your account,"

1197
01:30:36,900 --> 01:30:38,130
the voice insisted.

1198
01:30:38,130 --> 01:30:42,949
"Well, how do I know you're the bank? You
could be anyone," said Eddie. He had decided

1199
01:30:42,949 --> 01:30:46,710
to stay on the phone, but he wasn't going
to make it easy for the person at the other

1200
01:30:46,710 --> 01:30:47,710
end.

1201
01:30:47,710 --> 01:30:50,460
"I can assure you this is the CNTS bank calling."

1202
01:30:50,460 --> 01:30:55,739
"OK, then, well I can assure you that this
is Mr Munro. What do you want?"

1203
01:30:55,739 --> 01:31:00,900
"I can't do that, Mr Munro. I need to ask
some security questions."

1204
01:31:00,900 --> 01:31:05,269
"Well, my bank told me not to give my security
questions away."

1205
01:31:05,269 --> 01:31:06,729
"Mr Munro..."

1206
01:31:06,729 --> 01:31:13,320
"Ah, you don't know I am Mr Munro yet, do
you?" said Eddie. "When is your date of birth?"

1207
01:31:13,320 --> 01:31:16,179
"I'm not telling you that until you prove
you are the bank."

1208
01:31:16,179 --> 01:31:20,659
"All right, sir, ask me a question about your
account."

1209
01:31:20,659 --> 01:31:22,920
"OK, how much money is in my account?"

1210
01:31:22,920 --> 01:31:28,579
"I can't tell you that. I have to ask you
some security questions first." Eddie hung

1211
01:31:28,579 --> 01:31:29,920
up.

1212
01:31:29,920 --> 01:31:36,309
Thirty seconds later the phone rang again.
Eddie considered ignoring it, but he was bored

1213
01:31:36,309 --> 01:31:39,979
and was enjoying being in control for once.
"Hello?"

1214
01:31:39,979 --> 01:31:44,139
"Good morning, Mr Munro. This is CNTS bank..."

1215
01:31:44,139 --> 01:31:46,360
"Hi, how are you?"

1216
01:31:46,360 --> 01:31:52,309
The voice didn't know what to say for a moment,
but then sprang back into action. "I'm fine,

1217
01:31:52,309 --> 01:31:54,030
thank you, sir."

1218
01:31:54,030 --> 01:31:58,829
Eddie had to admit that the young man was
professional. If he was annoyed, he was hiding

1219
01:31:58,829 --> 01:32:05,480
it well. Eddie felt a little guilty - the
man was only doing his job. Then he thought

1220
01:32:05,480 --> 01:32:11,650
of Dominic and Neal and what bosses like them
would do to such youthful enthusiasm. He realized

1221
01:32:11,650 --> 01:32:17,239
that the voice was still speaking, but Eddie
wasn't paying attention. "Sorry? I wasn't

1222
01:32:17,239 --> 01:32:18,380
listening," he said.

1223
01:32:18,380 --> 01:32:23,449
"That's OK, sir. I was just saying that we
need to talk to you about your account, and

1224
01:32:23,449 --> 01:32:26,360
I can get my supervisor if you wish."

1225
01:32:26,360 --> 01:32:29,229
Eddie decided to give some ground. This was
getting boring.

1226
01:32:29,229 --> 01:32:33,960
"Go on, I believe you. You're CNTS bank. What
do you want?"

1227
01:32:33,960 --> 01:32:39,800
"Thank you, Mr Munro. I just need to ask you
some security questions. Is that OK?"

1228
01:32:39,800 --> 01:32:40,800
"Fine."

1229
01:32:40,800 --> 01:32:44,580
"Thank you. Can you confirm your telephone
banking password?"

1230
01:32:44,580 --> 01:32:45,580
"Chinatown."

1231
01:32:45,580 --> 01:32:51,090
"Thank you. And can you give me the second
and last numbers in your security code?"

1232
01:32:51,090 --> 01:32:52,650
"Eight and three."

1233
01:32:52,650 --> 01:32:54,829
"Thank you, Mr Munro."

1234
01:32:54,829 --> 01:32:56,570
"You're welcome."

1235
01:32:56,570 --> 01:32:58,820
"That completes the security with you."

1236
01:32:58,820 --> 01:33:00,880
"I'm so pleased."

1237
01:33:00,880 --> 01:33:06,989
"I was calling because your account had insufficient
funds to pay some direct debits this month,

1238
01:33:06,989 --> 01:33:11,090
and your credit card with us is now stopped
until you make further payments."

1239
01:33:11,090 --> 01:33:14,190
"Great. Thank you for telling me. Goodbye."

1240
01:33:14,190 --> 01:33:22,199
"No, Mr Munro. You are currently overdrawn
by 3,478.11 pounds, and the balance on your

1241
01:33:22,199 --> 01:33:31,110
credit card is 4,490.30 pounds I have to ask
if and when you will be making payments into

1242
01:33:31,110 --> 01:33:32,550
your account."

1243
01:33:32,550 --> 01:33:38,749
"I have no idea. I've lost my job and I can't
work. I'm thinking of doing the lottery on

1244
01:33:38,749 --> 01:33:43,191
Saturday, so give me a call on Monday and
I'll tell you if I can pay you or not. If

1245
01:33:43,191 --> 01:33:46,380
it helps, I'll enter my bank account number
and see if it wins."

1246
01:33:46,380 --> 01:33:52,409
"Mr Munro, my supervisor is here. He would
like to have a word with you. Would that be

1247
01:33:52,409 --> 01:33:53,409
OK?"

1248
01:33:53,409 --> 01:33:56,210
"Not really." Eddie hung up.

1249
01:33:56,210 --> 01:34:01,329
This time the phone did not ring again, which
surprised Eddie in a way. He walked slowly

1250
01:34:01,329 --> 01:34:06,590
into the kitchen, made a coffee, picked up
the newspaper and sat in an armchair to flick

1251
01:34:06,590 --> 01:34:10,280
through the pages to see what was on TV.

1252
01:34:10,280 --> 01:34:14,639
CHAPTER ELEVEN
After the fight

1253
01:34:14,639 --> 01:34:18,749
Eddie went back inside the ship and made his
way to the toilets, where he locked himself

1254
01:34:18,749 --> 01:34:25,190
inside a cubicle. He was shaking and sweating.
He sat down and put out his hands in front

1255
01:34:25,190 --> 01:34:31,010
of him, watching the shaking in fascination
and fear. He could feel the pain in his chest

1256
01:34:31,010 --> 01:34:37,039
now, and his ear was sore. He wiped his face
with the palm of his hand; there was blood

1257
01:34:37,039 --> 01:34:43,679
coming from his nose. He used some toilet
paper to stop the bleeding. He felt exhausted.

1258
01:34:43,679 --> 01:34:49,729
Eddie stayed where he was for about ten minutes.
The toilets were empty and no one else came

1259
01:34:49,729 --> 01:34:55,559
in during that time. He almost expected Dominic
to come in, and he imagined the fight starting

1260
01:34:55,559 --> 01:35:02,340
all over again. A struggle by the sinks, mirrors
breaking, doors slamming.

1261
01:35:02,340 --> 01:35:07,010
He decided to make his way back to the dining
room. He came out of the cubicle and looked

1262
01:35:07,010 --> 01:35:12,170
in the mirror to straighten his clothes and
his hair. The bleeding had stopped. He washed

1263
01:35:12,170 --> 01:35:13,170
his face.

1264
01:35:13,170 --> 01:35:20,170
The dance floor was full and the dining area
was being cleared. Lynn was at the table talking

1265
01:35:20,170 --> 01:35:22,579
to some other guests when Eddie found her.

1266
01:35:22,579 --> 01:35:28,550
"Hello, stranger," she said. "You took your
time. Where's Dominic?"

1267
01:35:28,550 --> 01:35:33,210
Eddie wasn't ready for a conversation about
this right now. "I couldn't find him."

1268
01:35:33,210 --> 01:35:35,309
"So where've you been all this time?"

1269
01:35:35,309 --> 01:35:40,079
"I went to get some fresh air, then I went
over to the Starlight Lounge and checked some

1270
01:35:40,079 --> 01:35:41,199
emails on the internet."

1271
01:35:41,199 --> 01:35:46,340
"Eddie, you're on holiday!" she said, putting
her arm around him.

1272
01:35:46,340 --> 01:35:47,729
"I know. Sorry."

1273
01:35:47,729 --> 01:35:50,469
"Come on, what do you want to drink?"

1274
01:35:50,469 --> 01:35:53,530
"I'll have a large scotch. No ice."

1275
01:35:53,530 --> 01:35:54,530
"Really?"

1276
01:35:54,530 --> 01:36:01,820
"Well, why not? We're on holiday." Eddie tried
to smile. His ear and nose were stinging.

1277
01:36:01,820 --> 01:36:05,110
His chest ached. Maybe he had a broken rib?

1278
01:36:05,110 --> 01:36:10,780
"OK. Wait here. I'll get them," she said,
and Eddie turned to watch the dancing and

1279
01:36:10,780 --> 01:36:17,280
the band. He was calmer now. The shock felt
less. He glanced over at the band and saw

1280
01:36:17,280 --> 01:36:23,340
Jen looking at him, and she gave a small wave.
He waved back, but suddenly wondered if she

1281
01:36:23,340 --> 01:36:31,530
was in fact waving to Dominic somehow. He
looked behind him, but Dominic wasn't there.

1282
01:36:31,530 --> 01:36:36,130
When Lynn came back, they had their drinks
and danced for a while. Eddie was tense the

1283
01:36:36,130 --> 01:36:41,249
whole time, waiting for Dominic to launch
a sudden attack on the table. Or maybe he

1284
01:36:41,249 --> 01:36:46,039
had gone back to his cabin to rest and would
wait until tomorrow or the next day to continue

1285
01:36:46,039 --> 01:36:47,409
the fight.

1286
01:36:47,409 --> 01:36:50,769
"I wonder where Dominic is?" said Lynn.

1287
01:36:50,769 --> 01:36:56,949
"No idea," said Eddie. "Come on. I'm tired.
Let's go to bed."

1288
01:36:56,949 --> 01:37:01,110
Even as they reached the cabin, Eddie was
looking around for Dominic, but he knew now

1289
01:37:01,110 --> 01:37:06,620
that he must have gone to his own cabin. He
felt relieved as they walked in, and he sat

1290
01:37:06,620 --> 01:37:09,699
down on the couch.

1291
01:37:09,699 --> 01:37:13,929
Lynn was looking in the mirror, taking off
her necklace and earrings. In the mirror she

1292
01:37:13,929 --> 01:37:18,150
watched Eddie sitting down. "You OK?" she
asked.

1293
01:37:18,150 --> 01:37:19,809
"Not really."

1294
01:37:19,809 --> 01:37:22,730
"What happened to your face?"

1295
01:37:22,730 --> 01:37:30,050
Eddie laughed briefly. He suddenly saw the
absurdity of it all. "I had a fight with Dominic,"

1296
01:37:30,050 --> 01:37:32,980
he said, looking at the bruises on his hands.

1297
01:37:32,980 --> 01:37:35,780
"You mean you had an argument?"

1298
01:37:35,780 --> 01:37:42,059
"No, I mean I had a fight. A proper fight.
You know, where people hit each other a few

1299
01:37:42,059 --> 01:37:47,210
times." He was trying to laugh again. But
the tears in his eyes and on his cheeks were

1300
01:37:47,210 --> 01:37:52,920
not happy ones. Lynn stopped what she was
doing and came to sit beside Eddie.

1301
01:37:52,920 --> 01:37:54,320
"You're shaking."

1302
01:37:54,320 --> 01:37:55,320
"Yeah."

1303
01:37:55,320 --> 01:37:57,830
"What happened?" she asked.

1304
01:37:57,830 --> 01:38:05,769
"To be honest, I can't really remember. It
all happened so fast. We were outside on deck

1305
01:38:05,769 --> 01:38:11,170
one minute, and the next I was trying to strangle
him." Eddie made a strangling gesture with

1306
01:38:11,170 --> 01:38:14,320
his hands, and again he saw that they were
shaking.

1307
01:38:14,320 --> 01:38:15,320
"What?"

1308
01:38:15,320 --> 01:38:21,699
"I know. I can't really believe it myself.
At one point I think he was going to pass

1309
01:38:21,699 --> 01:38:24,320
out. I almost pushed him over the side."

1310
01:38:24,320 --> 01:38:25,320
"Eddie!"

1311
01:38:25,320 --> 01:38:27,739
He was shaking his head.

1312
01:38:27,739 --> 01:38:31,380
"Was anyone watching all this? You must have
looked like madmen."

1313
01:38:31,380 --> 01:38:34,389
"No. It was just us. By the lifeboats."

1314
01:38:34,389 --> 01:38:37,769
"Where is he now?" asked Lynn.

1315
01:38:37,769 --> 01:38:42,860
"I don't know. I thought he followed me back
inside, but he must have gone back to his

1316
01:38:42,860 --> 01:38:44,540
cabin."

1317
01:38:44,540 --> 01:38:46,340
Lynn got Eddie a glass of water.

1318
01:38:46,340 --> 01:38:49,070
"Thanks," he said. "Sorry."

1319
01:38:49,070 --> 01:38:56,400
"I can't believe this. You're like a pair
of kids. It's one thing to find him on board,

1320
01:38:56,400 --> 01:38:59,230
but it's another to start fighting like kids
in a playground."

1321
01:38:59,230 --> 01:39:01,920
"He started it," said Eddie.

1322
01:39:01,920 --> 01:39:04,630
"Listen to yourself, Ed!"

1323
01:39:04,630 --> 01:39:06,159
"I know."

1324
01:39:06,159 --> 01:39:11,150
"Look, it's a shock that he's on the same
cruise, I admit, and I know it brings it all

1325
01:39:11,150 --> 01:39:16,949
back. But I thought the plan was to keep a
low profile now. Ignore him. Forget him."

1326
01:39:16,949 --> 01:39:20,420
"How can we forget him when he's on the same
cruise ship?"

1327
01:39:20,420 --> 01:39:27,429
"Well, we'll have to manage, and I suggest
we wait and see what happens. If he approaches

1328
01:39:27,429 --> 01:39:32,860
you at breakfast or something, don't get involved.
Apologise and walk away."

1329
01:39:32,860 --> 01:39:33,929
"Apologise?!"

1330
01:39:33,929 --> 01:39:39,969
"OK, well, maybe not apologise. Just ignore
him. Promise?"

1331
01:39:39,969 --> 01:39:44,559
"Yes, I promise," said Eddie.

1332
01:39:44,559 --> 01:39:50,159
CHAPTER TWELVE
Lynn and Eddie argue

1333
01:39:50,159 --> 01:39:54,909
Six months had passed since Eddie's departure
from Fenton's, and no work offers were coming

1334
01:39:54,909 --> 01:40:01,769
in. Summer was over and the evenings were
getting darker. Eddie had lost weight and

1335
01:40:01,769 --> 01:40:07,520
his relationship with Lynn was in a bad way.
Either they argued over most things or they

1336
01:40:07,520 --> 01:40:10,510
didn't speak at all.

1337
01:40:10,510 --> 01:40:15,659
One Thursday afternoon Lynn came in from work
and Eddie was sitting in his armchair as usual,

1338
01:40:15,659 --> 01:40:22,400
watching a TV show from America. A couple
and their neighbours were arguing over a dog.

1339
01:40:22,400 --> 01:40:25,920
Lynn was soaking wet. The rain was heavy outside.

1340
01:40:25,920 --> 01:40:33,059
"These people are so stupid," he said, not
looking up. "This guy says he can't sleep

1341
01:40:33,059 --> 01:40:37,570
because of his neighbours dog, and the neighbour
says the other guy's been shooting at it with

1342
01:40:37,570 --> 01:40:38,940
an air rifle!"

1343
01:40:38,940 --> 01:40:45,030
"It's OK. I'm fine, thanks. Don't get up,"
Lynn said, putting down heavy shopping bags

1344
01:40:45,030 --> 01:40:47,199
as she came through the front door.

1345
01:40:47,199 --> 01:40:52,690
"So this guy..." Eddie continued, "... the
guy with the dog, is suing the other guy for

1346
01:40:52,690 --> 01:40:56,190
a hundred thousand dollars in damages!"

1347
01:40:56,190 --> 01:41:01,349
Lynn was neither interested nor amused. She
took off her coat, picked up the bags and

1348
01:41:01,349 --> 01:41:06,140
went into the kitchen. On the way, she threw
the post on to the sofa.

1349
01:41:06,140 --> 01:41:12,230
"But the other guy - the guy with the gun
- he's suing the dog owner because he says

1350
01:41:12,230 --> 01:41:16,619
the dog barks all night and messes up his
garden."

1351
01:41:16,619 --> 01:41:21,739
Eddie knew he had already upset Lynn, but
he stayed where he was. She was always upset

1352
01:41:21,739 --> 01:41:26,880
these days. He decided to shout out the rest
of his commentary so that Lynn could hear

1353
01:41:26,880 --> 01:41:28,190
him in the kitchen.

1354
01:41:28,190 --> 01:41:33,360
"And now their wives are complaining that
the men are obsessed with arguing with each

1355
01:41:33,360 --> 01:41:37,949
other. They've been fighting over the dog
for three years, and now they both want a

1356
01:41:37,949 --> 01:41:40,099
divorce."

1357
01:41:40,099 --> 01:41:42,820
Eddie heard Lynn say something from the kitchen.

1358
01:41:42,820 --> 01:41:45,349
"What?" he shouted.

1359
01:41:45,349 --> 01:41:46,440
"Nothing."

1360
01:41:46,440 --> 01:41:50,679
"No, go on," he shouted. "What did you say?"

1361
01:41:50,679 --> 01:41:57,369
"Nothing. Go back to your show. It sounds
fascinating," she said. Eddie got up and went

1362
01:41:57,369 --> 01:42:00,829
to see her. "What's wrong?"

1363
01:42:00,829 --> 01:42:06,019
Lynn ignored him and started putting shopping
away in cupboards and in the fridge.

1364
01:42:06,019 --> 01:42:10,320
"What's wrong?" he asked again.

1365
01:42:10,320 --> 01:42:16,949
This time she stopped and looked at Eddie.
"Erm, well, let me see. I get up in the morning

1366
01:42:16,949 --> 01:42:22,079
and go to work while you sit and watch telly.
I come in from work, and you're still sitting

1367
01:42:22,079 --> 01:42:27,429
and watching telly. I do the shopping, I get
no help. I do the cooking, I get no help.

1368
01:42:27,429 --> 01:42:32,070
I try to talk to you, and I get nothing. You
used to have breakfast with me in the mornings,

1369
01:42:32,070 --> 01:42:37,510
and now you don't get up at all! We never
go out. Our friends don't call us. The house

1370
01:42:37,510 --> 01:42:41,900
is a mess, and you're here all day making
it messier. You don't clean up, you don't

1371
01:42:41,900 --> 01:42:44,660
tidy. You look a mess..."

1372
01:42:44,660 --> 01:42:46,090
"Thanks very much."

1373
01:42:46,090 --> 01:42:51,530
"... and I don't hear anything positive from
you about anything. Anything! I'm sick of

1374
01:42:51,530 --> 01:42:52,590
it."

1375
01:42:52,590 --> 01:42:55,659
There was a pause after she stopped.

1376
01:42:55,659 --> 01:42:57,929
"Bad day then?" he said.

1377
01:42:57,929 --> 01:43:04,760
"It's not funny, Eddie. I worry so much about
you, your job situation, money - and then

1378
01:43:04,760 --> 01:43:09,610
I go into work and I have at least twenty
- five kids in my class all day. I try to

1379
01:43:09,610 --> 01:43:15,340
keep them under control and happy, but I just
want to cry. I want to tell them all to shut

1380
01:43:15,340 --> 01:43:20,920
up. I want to tell them to enjoy drawing pictures
and singing songs, because after that life

1381
01:43:20,920 --> 01:43:22,150
is pointless."

1382
01:43:22,150 --> 01:43:25,400
"So, you did have a bad day."

1383
01:43:25,400 --> 01:43:28,440
"Bad year, Eddie. Bad year."

1384
01:43:28,440 --> 01:43:31,479
"So it's all my fault?"

1385
01:43:31,479 --> 01:43:33,829
"That is not what I mean."

1386
01:43:33,829 --> 01:43:34,829
"Yeah, right."

1387
01:43:34,829 --> 01:43:42,229
At that point, Lynn picked up a full box of
eggs and threw it at Eddie. He ducked just

1388
01:43:42,229 --> 01:43:45,800
in time, and the whole thing exploded on the
kitchen wall.

1389
01:43:45,800 --> 01:43:51,840
"I guess we can have omelets for dinner,"
said Eddie, but he knew things had gone too

1390
01:43:51,840 --> 01:43:52,840
far.

1391
01:43:52,840 --> 01:43:56,730
"You can have omelets for dinner. I'm going
out."

1392
01:43:56,730 --> 01:43:57,889
"Where to?"

1393
01:43:57,889 --> 01:44:00,599
"I'm going to Angela's."

1394
01:44:00,599 --> 01:44:04,650
"Angela's? That's two hours away. When will
you be back?"

1395
01:44:04,650 --> 01:44:05,659
"Saturday."

1396
01:44:05,659 --> 01:44:06,670
"Saturday?"

1397
01:44:06,670 --> 01:44:10,600
"Maybe Sunday. I don't know."

1398
01:44:10,600 --> 01:44:12,080
"Lynn, please."

1399
01:44:12,080 --> 01:44:19,599
"No, Eddie. I've had enough. We're broke - worse
than broke - we are in so much debt. You've

1400
01:44:19,599 --> 01:44:23,780
got no job and you can't get a job, or you
don't want one. I don't know."

1401
01:44:23,780 --> 01:44:25,090
"Lynn, listen to me."

1402
01:44:25,090 --> 01:44:28,519
"You sit in the house all day, feeling sorry
for yourself..."

1403
01:44:28,519 --> 01:44:29,519
"Lynn..."

1404
01:44:29,519 --> 01:44:30,900
She was crying now.

1405
01:44:30,900 --> 01:44:36,421
"... and it isn't getting better," she sobbed.
"It's getting worse and I hate it. I'm sorry

1406
01:44:36,421 --> 01:44:42,350
you lost your job, and I'm sorry it made you
ill. I'm sorry I'm not strong enough now,

1407
01:44:42,350 --> 01:44:50,929
but I can't help you anymore. I tried. I've
lost you. You're here, but you're not here.

1408
01:44:50,929 --> 01:44:54,920
I want a break. We want a break."

1409
01:44:54,920 --> 01:44:58,349
"No, Lynn. Please, we have to talk..."

1410
01:44:58,349 --> 01:45:01,369
"I'll call you when I get to Angela's."

1411
01:45:01,369 --> 01:45:05,710
She was walking out of the kitchen and into
the hall. She opened the door under the stairs

1412
01:45:05,710 --> 01:45:10,729
and took out an overnight bag. Eddie could
see she had already packed it.

1413
01:45:10,729 --> 01:45:14,340
"I don't believe this. You're leaving me?"

1414
01:45:14,340 --> 01:45:19,539
"No. I'll be back on Sunday. Maybe. I don't
know."

1415
01:45:19,539 --> 01:45:26,900
"This is ridiculous. You can't go. Lynn, we've
been together for ten years."

1416
01:45:26,900 --> 01:45:28,400
She was putting on her coat.

1417
01:45:28,400 --> 01:45:30,039
"What about your job?"

1418
01:45:30,039 --> 01:45:36,449
"I don't care about the job. You don't care
about work. Now I don't care about work."

1419
01:45:36,449 --> 01:45:40,800
She was walking down the hall towards the
front door. Eddie grabbed her arm.

1420
01:45:40,800 --> 01:45:42,510
"Get your hands off me."

1421
01:45:42,510 --> 01:45:43,510
"Lynn."

1422
01:45:43,510 --> 01:45:45,570
"Get your hands off me!"

1423
01:45:45,570 --> 01:45:47,989
He let go.

1424
01:45:47,989 --> 01:45:50,409
"Lynn, I'm sorry."

1425
01:45:50,409 --> 01:45:55,940
But she had walked out of the door and got
into her car, and was driving down the road.

1426
01:45:55,940 --> 01:46:01,459
Eddie stood in the doorway and watched the
car disappear. The rain had stopped, but the

1427
01:46:01,459 --> 01:46:08,300
clouds were ready for another storm. He went
back inside and the house felt very strange.

1428
01:46:08,300 --> 01:46:14,170
Panic was in his mind, heart and stomach.
The kitchen door was open, and he saw broken

1429
01:46:14,170 --> 01:46:17,639
eggs dripping off the clock and down the wall.

1430
01:46:17,639 --> 01:46:22,330
He sat down on the sofa. The neighbours were
still arguing about the dog, which was now

1431
01:46:22,330 --> 01:46:28,179
in the studio, and a dog psychologist was
trying to talk to it. This time last year

1432
01:46:28,179 --> 01:46:33,360
he was in Moscow working on the project of
his career with good money in the bank, and

1433
01:46:33,360 --> 01:46:39,000
he and Lynn had even discussed starting a
family. Now, he had lost his job, his money,

1434
01:46:39,000 --> 01:46:45,030
his health, his confidence, and even his wife.
Instead of taking the company to the next

1435
01:46:45,030 --> 01:46:52,290
level and building a future, he was sitting
in his lounge watching a dog in therapy.

1436
01:46:52,290 --> 01:46:57,190
He looked around for the remote control to
change channels, and saw the post. There were

1437
01:46:57,190 --> 01:47:01,920
some letters for Lynn, the new programme for
the theatre, more bills, and a letter from

1438
01:47:01,920 --> 01:47:08,630
Steve Scott, his solicitor. He knew what the
letter said before he opened it. It was the

1439
01:47:08,630 --> 01:47:13,750
result of many difficult meetings with his
solicitor and financial adviser. The letter

1440
01:47:13,750 --> 01:47:16,750
now confirmed that he was bankrupt.

1441
01:47:16,750 --> 01:47:18,059
Bankrupt.

1442
01:47:18,059 --> 01:47:20,679
A death.

1443
01:47:20,679 --> 01:47:24,059
The end of a life with money.

1444
01:47:24,059 --> 01:47:30,639
For a few more minutes Eddie watched two American
adults fighting and a dog being hypnotized.

